Segge
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="1B1ECE732968ECE720BDCBED597472B8" pageId="null" pageNumber="459" type="description">
<paragraph id="F40B853E92B4CDB461F6BB52672C7A37" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">
3-10 cm hoch; Wuchsform und 
<normalizedToken id="780D8EFBDF5E695E7EB5A917EDF002CF" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="FCC0DE40301560CEB76050F7E5CB4B83" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="459" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digitata">
<emphasis id="9BC9A8CEAC991B7321EE431C91FBDE1E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">C. digitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr.55). 
<emphasis id="0D189530A5A3CE0BF6FDFEC9003A6235" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">
Die Stengel stets bogig 
<normalizedToken id="FF6557D1BE9B238274F4CCCB54E9DA45" originalValue="zurückgekrümmt" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">zurueckgekruemmt</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="AE587BB7C5AA05EC653275F6384F75F3" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="38F3B54575CF11BE069678266223B4B7" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="459" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornithopoda">
<emphasis id="263BC78F5BF791BC7FF16A95D224EC9F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">C. ornithopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 56), die 
<normalizedToken id="9945B74B7D597E520423D879BD7768DA" originalValue="Ähren" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Aehren</normalizedToken>
aber kleiner und mit weniger 
<normalizedToken id="F104C0512A83DF4780F3F73599F33C3B" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Blueten</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="F39E453D9FE51AF808E6439EF9BF93F0" originalValue="Tragblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Tragblaetter</normalizedToken>
⅔ bis so lang wie die reifen 
<normalizedToken id="300CBAA6B1B9329927A8400F1AC2CF10" originalValue="Fruchtschläuche" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Fruchtschlaeuche</normalizedToken>
, in der Form wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="F45761F5C69EA71EF7C9435F26DEDFC3" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="459" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digitata">
<emphasis id="11BD81DDD14DC6C71FDC86DD22F0831E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">C. digitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meist 
<emphasis id="AB79ACF1CF2A6F89D43D67FF740EAD0D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">dunkelrotbraun.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="780D90E48EAAE6AF9A122053B3861DC7" originalValue="Fruchtschläuche" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Fruchtschlaeuche</normalizedToken>
2-3,5 mm lang, in der Form wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="3049BB6125C34281CF450CE6438276B4" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="459" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digitata">
<emphasis id="625EBBA28DED06CAEA8BFC3CB7694CCA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">C. digitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, jedoch 
<emphasis id="82C90A12505E017FFDBCE071AC5BA6B9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">
<normalizedToken id="DFDD29BC0A8128F6440AB13F1F580D77" originalValue="vollständig" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">vollstaendig</normalizedToken>
kahl
</emphasis>
, dunkelbraun und 
<emphasis id="10318946D7EB395A6CD63FE6A7F8D5F6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">
auffallend 
<normalizedToken id="8F50C3BA5C3C1350E3473D433FC3932C" originalValue="glänzend" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">glaenzend</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
Narben 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F5303683CA86A0489C8B88B6790AF9C" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="F15A738D56252306401AEB798D720618" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Zytologische Angaben.</emphasis>
Keine Untersuchungen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A9FDDFA5E281E6BB11AC3EE48F27F173" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="1232D97D0BBEC4351951110C1603B33F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Standort.</emphasis>
Subalpin und alpin. 
<normalizedToken id="E8450172229277CDFE97ED1252D441E7" originalValue="Ständig" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Staendig</normalizedToken>
durchfeuchteter, kalkhaltiger Ruhschutt in Mulden mit ziemlich langer Schneebedeckung (7-9 Monate), 
<emphasis id="4FCF567DC9E8D7C87049916F513986BF" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Salicetum retuso-reticulatae</emphasis>
Br.-Bl. 1926; zudem auf Graten im 
<emphasis id="12D6C5E9EEAD26D926E75957B35DD4CB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Caricetum firmae</emphasis>
Br.-Bl. 1926.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41858CDC505D905CC9295B5A2823E962" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="E1216010B403DE9083BCD5BE572517ED" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">
Verbreitung. Mittel- und 
<normalizedToken id="061DB86098BB8F2744E24F5A4F155A69" originalValue="südeuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">suedeuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Gebirgspflanze:
</emphasis>
Nordspanische Gebirge, Alpen (von den Seealpen bis 
<normalizedToken id="8890150969D4C70353AC29E8BC6DE066" originalValue="Kärnten" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Kaernten</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="7D577EC4B82449E569D8411B4F715EA6" originalValue="Niederösterreich" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Niederoesterreich</normalizedToken>
), Gebirge der Balkanhalbinsel. - Im Gebiet in den Alpen (
<normalizedToken id="C1A5191CF93B876F8EAB97FBC1EFD1B0" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Grigna am Comersee) verbreitet; ziemlich selten.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31E71998A87102C4B041043FDE4D9DD1" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="98110EAC6B0CD68F60263DB5C2C6F783" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Siehe unter 
<taxonomicName id="F8E7FA8305F9DB5C273DB5EC5CE54725" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="459" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornithopoda">
<emphasis id="AABB680F88C702729C4C22A9C2ABCB73" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="459">C. ornithopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 56).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
